OL,3,CCancelling King's US visit would be a
OL,4,C'mistake' says Trump's ambassador to UK
OL,6,FHowever, his ambassador in London was
OL,7,Fdoing a much better job of trans-
OL,8,FAtlantic diplomacy at the business
OL,9,Fconference saying: "While there has
OL,10,Fnot been any direct engagement by the
OL,11,FUK or any NATO country militarily
OL,12,Fother than defensive, the intelligence
OL,13,Fhas been vital and very useful to the
OL,14,FUnited States and Israel".
OL,26,@vD@YO]
